WEBVTT

00:09.096 --> 00:09.313
.

00:09.357 --> 00:11.141
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:11.185 --> 00:12.534
the people are represented

00:12.577 --> 00:15.145
by two separate,
yet equally important groups:

00:15.189 --> 00:17.104
the police,
who investigate crime,

00:17.147 --> 00:19.715
and the district attorneys,
who prosecute the offenders.

00:19.758 --> 00:21.499
These are their stories.

00:21.543 --> 00:22.718
[dramatic musical sting]

00:24.111 --> 00:25.677
- Great jacket.

00:25.721 --> 00:27.549
- Thanks.
- Are you a model or something?

00:27.592 --> 00:29.159
- Ugh.

00:29.203 --> 00:30.334
- Really? You're offended

00:30.378 --> 00:31.596
because I paid you
a compliment?

00:31.640 --> 00:33.163
- I didn't ask you
to compliment me, did I?

00:33.207 --> 00:34.556
No.

00:34.599 --> 00:36.079
I'm just trying to walk
to the damn subway,

00:36.123 --> 00:38.168
now back up and get the hell
out of my way.

00:38.212 --> 00:39.561
- Get the hell
out of your way?

00:39.604 --> 00:41.084
Who do you think
you're talking to, sweetie?

00:41.128 --> 00:42.825
Are you serious?
You're gonna record me?

00:42.868 --> 00:44.305
We're just talking.

00:44.348 --> 00:47.525
- I said back up and get
the hell out of my way.

00:47.569 --> 00:49.310
- Have a wonderful night, miss.

00:49.353 --> 00:50.746
Pleasure talking to you.

00:55.229 --> 00:57.187
[gunshots]

00:57.231 --> 01:00.190
[tense music]

01:00.234 --> 01:07.197
♪

01:07.241 --> 01:08.372
[phone beeping]

01:08.416 --> 01:09.895
[line ringing]

01:09.939 --> 01:11.549
- 911. What's your emergency?

01:11.593 --> 01:13.595
- Yeah, a man's been shot.
- What's your location?

01:13.638 --> 01:15.336
- On the corner of West 173rd
and Fort Washington.

01:15.379 --> 01:16.598
- What's his status?
- Please.

01:16.641 --> 01:18.208
Please, he's bleeding.

01:18.252 --> 01:21.211
[siren blaring]

01:22.908 --> 01:24.562
- I hear he was on the job?

01:24.606 --> 01:25.868
- Took two to the chest.

01:25.911 --> 01:27.826
Recovered the casing
near the body. 9mm.

01:27.870 --> 01:29.741
- Mm-hmm.
- Any witnesses?

01:29.785 --> 01:32.875
- No. Nothing yet, anyway.

01:32.918 --> 01:34.442
Name was James Doyle.

01:34.485 --> 01:36.139
Detective First Grade.

01:36.183 --> 01:38.707
[tense music]

01:38.750 --> 01:43.581
♪

01:43.625 --> 01:45.192
- Jimmy.

01:46.454 --> 01:48.282
He goes by Jimmy, not James.

01:51.198 --> 01:53.548
- Oh. Sorry.

01:54.853 --> 01:56.507
- I'll see you on
the other side, brother.

01:56.551 --> 02:02.513
♪

02:04.559 --> 02:07.518
[dramatic music]

02:07.562 --> 02:14.308
♪

02:34.676 --> 02:41.596
♪

02:50.344 --> 02:51.519
- Good evening.

02:51.562 --> 02:54.478
At approximately
10:05 this evening,

02:54.522 --> 02:56.480
Detective First Grade
James Doyle

02:56.524 --> 02:59.309
was shot and killed
while working off duty.

02:59.353 --> 03:02.791
Jimmy was a 23-year veteran
of the NYPD

03:02.834 --> 03:05.315
and a recipient of multiple
awards and accommodations,

03:05.359 --> 03:06.925
including the Medal of Valor,

03:06.969 --> 03:10.233
which is awarded for
outstanding personal bravery,

03:10.277 --> 03:12.366
intelligently performing
in the line of duty

03:12.409 --> 03:14.324
and imminent hazard to life...

03:14.368 --> 03:16.239
- Did you see anyone
in the immediate vicinity?

03:16.283 --> 03:17.893
- No.
- No one?

03:17.936 --> 03:19.851
You didn't see anyone running
or jumping into a car?

03:19.895 --> 03:21.505
- No.

03:21.549 --> 03:23.681
I'm sorry, I was so focused
on the man who got shot.

03:23.725 --> 03:25.683
- How far away were you when
you heard the two loud pops?

03:25.727 --> 03:27.468
- I don't know.

03:27.511 --> 03:29.252
About 30 yards.

03:29.296 --> 03:32.342
- And you ran toward
the sound of the gunshots,

03:32.386 --> 03:34.039
which means you were there
five or six seconds

03:34.083 --> 03:36.346
after the shooting.
- What's your point?

03:36.390 --> 03:38.348
- My point is I find it hard to
believe you didn't see anybody.

03:38.392 --> 03:39.480
- Hey, come on, Frank.

03:39.523 --> 03:40.742
- I'm just trying
to motivate her.

03:40.785 --> 03:42.352
- Okay, okay.

03:42.396 --> 03:43.962
You know what, ma'am?

03:44.006 --> 03:45.486
If you can think
of anything else

03:45.529 --> 03:47.444
that might be helpful to us,
give us a call.

03:47.488 --> 03:48.706
Thank you.

03:48.750 --> 03:50.055
Hey.

03:50.099 --> 03:52.884
We're gonna have to take
this one step at a time.

03:52.928 --> 03:54.451
- Let's go.

03:54.495 --> 03:57.062
We need to talk
to Jimmy's wife.

03:57.106 --> 03:58.542
- Yeah, okay.

03:59.935 --> 04:01.371
- Excuse me.

04:01.415 --> 04:03.765
[indistinct chatter]

04:04.940 --> 04:06.333
- Hey.

04:08.770 --> 04:10.598
- Hey, cuz.

04:11.468 --> 04:12.687
- Heather.

04:12.730 --> 04:14.732
- Frankie.

04:14.776 --> 04:17.344
- I am so sorry.
I can't believe this happened.

04:18.997 --> 04:21.478
Heather, this is my partner,
Kevin Bernard.

04:21.522 --> 04:23.306
- So sorry about your loss.

04:26.527 --> 04:28.355
- Is there somewhere we can...

04:32.446 --> 04:33.925
- Hey, guys,
can we have the room?

04:33.969 --> 04:35.623
Thanks.

04:43.935 --> 04:45.589
- [sighs] I hate to do this.

04:45.633 --> 04:47.330
- I understand.

04:47.374 --> 04:48.462
It's fine.

04:49.985 --> 04:52.640
- You have any idea who
might've done this to Jimmy?

04:52.683 --> 04:55.338
- No.
- Was he having any problems,

04:55.382 --> 04:57.079
anything unusual going on
in his life?

04:57.122 --> 04:59.777
- No. He was doing great.

04:59.821 --> 05:02.040
- Were there any
recent arguments,

05:02.084 --> 05:04.304
confrontations?
- Not sure.

05:07.089 --> 05:09.831
We split up about
three years ago.

05:09.874 --> 05:11.572
- Oh, I-I didn't know.

05:11.615 --> 05:13.617
I'm sorry, I--

05:13.661 --> 05:15.967
Jimmy and I, we haven't
talked in a while, so...

05:16.011 --> 05:18.100
- Sometimes life
gets in the way.

05:18.143 --> 05:19.710
Just the way it is.

05:19.754 --> 05:22.670
[somber music]

05:22.713 --> 05:24.802
But we were still really close.

05:26.543 --> 05:28.110
Talked to him every day.

05:30.504 --> 05:31.809
'Cause he was my best friend.

05:31.853 --> 05:34.421
[crying]

05:38.860 --> 05:41.993
- You have any idea
why he was up on 173rd Street?

05:42.037 --> 05:45.910
♪

05:45.954 --> 05:49.392
- How long were
you and Jimmy dating?

05:49.436 --> 05:50.915
- Almost three years.

05:53.744 --> 05:55.485
I still can't believe this.

05:56.704 --> 05:58.053
We had dinner last night.

05:58.096 --> 05:59.663
He said that he had
to get up early

05:59.707 --> 06:02.666
and take his kids to school,
so...

06:02.710 --> 06:05.016
[sighs] He was gonna
head back to Brooklyn

06:05.060 --> 06:06.975
and sleep at his apartment.

06:07.018 --> 06:08.977
- What'd you two do for dinner?

06:09.020 --> 06:11.153
- We went to a place
on Broadway called Tarravita.

06:11.196 --> 06:13.024
It's a few blocks this way.

06:13.068 --> 06:14.809
- Hmm.

06:14.852 --> 06:17.420
Anything out of the ordinary
happen at dinner last night?

06:17.464 --> 06:19.770
Someone staring at Jimmy? You?

06:19.814 --> 06:20.902
- No.

06:20.945 --> 06:22.860
It was a nice, normal dinner.

06:22.904 --> 06:25.167
- What about walking home?

06:25.210 --> 06:27.778
- I didn't notice
anything unusual.

06:27.822 --> 06:29.214
- Hmm.

06:29.258 --> 06:30.825
- [sighs]

06:36.961 --> 06:39.007
It's not fair.

06:39.050 --> 06:40.661
It's just not.

06:43.011 --> 06:45.187
Jimmy was special.

06:45.230 --> 06:47.624
- I know.
Jimmy and I were friends.

06:47.668 --> 06:50.105
- So you know what I mean.

06:50.148 --> 06:53.238
He loved being a cop, too,
more than anything.

06:53.282 --> 06:55.937
Despite all the protests
and anti-police hate.

06:55.980 --> 06:58.722
- Probably not so easy
for you though.

06:58.766 --> 07:00.985
- You're right.

07:01.029 --> 07:04.162
A lot of my friends
didn't understand how...

07:04.206 --> 07:06.556
a Black woman
could date a cop.

07:06.600 --> 07:08.471
A white cop no less.

07:08.515 --> 07:10.647
- Any of these friends ever
get in an argument with Jimmy?

07:11.996 --> 07:13.563
- No.

07:13.607 --> 07:15.130
- Anyone ever threaten
you or harass you?

07:21.571 --> 07:23.617
- That's--that's you, right?

07:24.966 --> 07:26.794
Last night.

07:26.837 --> 07:29.927
Eight minutes
before Detective Doyle

07:29.971 --> 07:31.625
was shot and killed.

07:34.541 --> 07:36.543
- I went over there.

07:36.586 --> 07:38.066
I live five blocks away.

07:38.109 --> 07:41.809
So I walk over there sometimes
hoping to bump into her.

07:41.852 --> 07:43.593
All right?
We worked together at a hotel.

07:43.637 --> 07:45.595
We dated for a few months,
nothing serious.

07:45.639 --> 07:47.118
Then she starts
seeing this dude Jimmy

07:47.162 --> 07:48.990
and I still have strong
feelings for Ezrie.

07:49.033 --> 07:50.644
You know, what can I say, man?

07:50.687 --> 07:52.733
Listen, I get a little
obsessive sometimes.

07:52.776 --> 07:54.865
- Obsessive enough
to kill someone.

07:54.909 --> 07:55.910
- No.
- Yeah.

07:55.953 --> 07:57.520
- No. Hell no.

07:57.564 --> 07:58.869
I had nothing to do
with that shooting.

07:58.913 --> 08:01.481
I don't even own a gun.
- Let's see this again.

08:02.786 --> 08:05.093
You walk out at 9:58.

08:05.136 --> 08:07.791
The 911 call comes in at 10:04.

08:07.835 --> 08:09.532
- That's you. Where'd you go?

08:09.576 --> 08:10.794
What'd you do? Hmm?

08:10.838 --> 08:12.317
What'd you do?

08:12.361 --> 08:14.624
- I saw Ezrie and Jimmy
at the front door.

08:14.668 --> 08:15.886
Okay?

08:15.930 --> 08:17.975
He kissed her goodnight.
He walked away.

08:18.019 --> 08:19.629
I thought about
ringing the buzzer,

08:19.673 --> 08:21.805
but I knew that'd be a bad
idea so I started walking home.

08:21.849 --> 08:24.721
- Right about the time
Detective Jimmy Doyle was shot.

08:24.765 --> 08:26.593
- Yeah, I heard the shots.

08:26.636 --> 08:28.116
It sounded like two loud pops.
- Loud?

08:28.159 --> 08:30.335
So you were close.

08:30.379 --> 08:33.338
Meaning you probably
saw the shooting too.

08:33.382 --> 08:35.079
- No. No.

08:35.123 --> 08:37.168
I heard the gunshots.
I didn't really see anything.

08:37.212 --> 08:38.256
- What does that even mean,

08:38.300 --> 08:39.693
you "didn't really
see anything"?

08:39.736 --> 08:41.956
- It means I didn't see
the shooter or shooting.

08:43.784 --> 08:45.916
All I saw was some white dude
running down Broadway.

08:45.960 --> 08:47.875
He looked scared as hell.

08:49.180 --> 08:50.704
- Oh, yeah? When was this?

08:50.747 --> 08:53.010
- It was about 10 seconds
after the gunshots.

08:53.054 --> 08:55.796
[tense music]

08:55.839 --> 08:59.974
♪

09:00.017 --> 09:03.064
- This is 12 seconds
after the 911 call.

09:04.718 --> 09:06.763
- Let's hold off on
getting a warrant for now.

09:06.807 --> 09:08.199
We need to find out
who this guy is

09:08.243 --> 09:09.853
and why the hell he's running.

09:09.897 --> 09:11.028
- So I already ran
a reverse image search.

09:11.072 --> 09:12.377
His name is Scott Gleacher.

09:12.421 --> 09:13.901
He works at an investment firm
in Midtown.

09:15.685 --> 09:17.905
- We need to track his ass down
right now.

09:17.948 --> 09:19.080
- Yeah.

09:24.651 --> 09:25.042
.

09:25.086 --> 09:26.522
- Yeah, that's me.

09:26.566 --> 09:27.784
So?

09:27.828 --> 09:29.220
- So?

09:29.264 --> 09:30.657
It's gonna be like that?

09:30.700 --> 09:32.136
- Excuse me?

09:32.180 --> 09:34.008
- A police officer
was shot and killed

09:34.051 --> 09:37.011
about 75 yards away
from where you were running.

09:39.361 --> 09:41.319
- I want to help out, but--

09:41.363 --> 09:43.234
- But what?

09:43.278 --> 09:45.585
- I'm not answering questions
without a lawyer present.

09:48.152 --> 09:49.719
Here's his name and number.

09:49.763 --> 09:52.417
You want to talk about this,
call.

10:00.600 --> 10:02.427
- He has no priors.

10:02.471 --> 10:04.647
- No guns registered
in his name either.

10:04.691 --> 10:06.344
- Any connection
between him and Doyle?

10:06.388 --> 10:08.042
- No. Nothing.

10:08.085 --> 10:11.436
- So some rich Wall Street dude
with no rap sheet

10:11.480 --> 10:13.134
decides to shoot
an off-duty cop

10:13.177 --> 10:14.309
that he doesn't even know?

10:14.352 --> 10:16.050
- I know.
It doesn't make any sense.

10:16.093 --> 10:18.052
- And if he's so innocent,
why not cooperate?

10:18.095 --> 10:19.531
Why not just tell us
what he saw

10:19.575 --> 10:20.794
and why he was running?

10:20.837 --> 10:22.186
- What the hell
was Gleacher doing

10:22.230 --> 10:23.579
up in Washington Heights
in the first place?

10:23.623 --> 10:26.538
I mean, he lives in Tribeca,
he works in Midtown.

10:26.582 --> 10:28.497
- Looks he like was
at some charity event.

10:28.540 --> 10:30.455
This photo was posted
at 8:55 p.m.

10:30.499 --> 10:32.370
- Where was he?

10:32.414 --> 10:34.634
- TeamGirl Inc.

10:34.677 --> 10:36.200
It's a nonprofit
that's dedicated

10:36.244 --> 10:37.767
to empowering
at-risk teenage girls.

10:37.811 --> 10:39.682
- Location?

10:39.726 --> 10:40.683
- It's Washington Heights.

10:40.727 --> 10:42.598
2243 165th Street.

10:45.340 --> 10:47.168
[dramatic musical sting]

10:47.211 --> 10:48.691
- Of course I know
Scott Gleacher.

10:48.735 --> 10:50.693
He's one of the founders
of TeamGirl.

10:50.737 --> 10:53.609
He just donated $1 million,
helped us pay for all this.

10:53.653 --> 10:55.350
- Was he at the event
last night?

10:55.393 --> 10:56.525
- Of course.

10:56.568 --> 10:58.396
He was the guest of honor.
- Oh.

10:58.440 --> 11:02.400
- Was Mr. Gleacher involved
in any unusual activity?

11:02.444 --> 11:04.098
- What do you mean?

11:04.141 --> 11:05.490
- Was there any arguments
or confrontations?

11:05.534 --> 11:07.101
- No.

11:07.144 --> 11:08.624
- Hmm.

11:08.668 --> 11:10.321
Have you ever seen
this man before?

11:10.365 --> 11:13.585
- No, doesn't look familiar.
Sorry.

11:13.629 --> 11:15.892
- Thank you for your time.

11:15.936 --> 11:17.546
- If you don't mind,

11:17.589 --> 11:19.635
why are you asking
about Scott Gleacher?

11:19.679 --> 11:21.768
- He's a person of interest
in a homicide.

11:24.509 --> 11:27.208
- I've only met him
a few times...

11:27.251 --> 11:28.644
but there have definitely been

11:28.688 --> 11:30.646
a lot of rumors swirling
lately.

11:32.779 --> 11:35.390
- What sort of rumors?

11:35.433 --> 11:37.653
- I've been working for
TeamGirl for about a year now.

11:37.697 --> 11:39.829
I started going to meetings
when I was in high school.

11:39.873 --> 11:41.701
It was great.

11:41.744 --> 11:43.703
It really motivated me to get
good grades and go to college.

11:43.746 --> 11:44.878
- So you're in college now?

11:44.921 --> 11:46.357
- Yeah. Fordham.

11:46.401 --> 11:48.446
- Oh. Good for you.

11:48.490 --> 11:51.754
- You work at TeamGirl.
You must know Scott Gleacher.

11:51.798 --> 11:53.930
- Yeah, I know Scott.

11:53.974 --> 11:57.151
- Are you two
romantically involved?

11:59.283 --> 12:00.632
- Sort of.

12:00.676 --> 12:02.417
We hang out sometimes.

12:02.460 --> 12:03.548
- Hmm.

12:03.592 --> 12:04.680
[door rattles]

12:06.813 --> 12:08.379
- What's going on?

12:08.423 --> 12:09.641
- Oh.

12:09.685 --> 12:11.382
We're investigating a homicide.

12:12.732 --> 12:14.821
- What's that got to do
with my sister?

12:14.864 --> 12:17.301
- Nothing.
At the moment anyways.

12:17.345 --> 12:20.609
We're more concerned about
her friend Scott Gleacher.

12:20.652 --> 12:22.785
- Were you at that
party last night?

12:22.829 --> 12:24.439
- No, it was for rich people.

12:24.482 --> 12:26.789
They were trying
to raise money.

12:26.833 --> 12:30.837
- Forgive me for asking,
but I noticed...

12:30.880 --> 12:33.709
you have some stitches
above your right eye.

12:33.753 --> 12:34.971
What happened?

12:35.015 --> 12:36.668
- Don't answer that, sweetie.

12:36.712 --> 12:38.583
- I'm sorry,
I didn't mean to pry.

12:38.627 --> 12:42.674
Just noticed some bruising and
stitches, so I thought I'd ask.

12:42.718 --> 12:44.851
- She's doing fine.
- That's good to hear.

12:44.894 --> 12:48.550
Just one more question,
then we'll go on our way.

12:48.593 --> 12:50.291
Do you know anything
about that policeman

12:50.334 --> 12:51.901
who was shot last night?

12:51.945 --> 12:53.990
- She doesn't.
Now, if you don't mind--

12:54.034 --> 12:55.775
- I'm just trying
to ask her a--

12:55.818 --> 12:57.472
- She's not gonna answer
any more questions.

12:57.515 --> 12:58.865
Now please leave.

12:58.908 --> 13:01.781
[tense music]

13:01.824 --> 13:02.912
♪

13:02.956 --> 13:04.479
- Thank you.

13:04.522 --> 13:10.790
♪

13:10.833 --> 13:12.356
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

13:12.400 --> 13:13.793
- How you doing?

13:13.836 --> 13:15.359
- Thanks for meeting with us.
- Sure. What's up?

13:15.403 --> 13:17.622
- A woman named Regina Daniels

13:17.666 --> 13:19.276
was treated
at New York Presbyterian

13:19.320 --> 13:21.278
about three days ago.

13:21.322 --> 13:22.540
She got admitted to the ER

13:22.584 --> 13:24.368
with a gash
above her right eye.

13:24.412 --> 13:26.283
Hospital said
they contacted SVU about

13:26.327 --> 13:27.807
possible domestic abuse.

13:27.850 --> 13:29.460
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
I remember her.

13:29.504 --> 13:32.637
She said that
she hit her head on a table.

13:32.681 --> 13:34.726
- You're not buying it?
- No, I'm not.

13:34.770 --> 13:36.903
She insisted
that she was telling the truth

13:36.946 --> 13:39.383
and went on to tell me
that she and her boyfriend

13:39.427 --> 13:40.820
were madly in love.

13:40.863 --> 13:42.734
I tried to talk to her,
but no dice.

13:42.778 --> 13:45.737
- She ever say anything
about Detective Jimmy Doyle?

13:45.781 --> 13:47.565
- No.
Why would she bring him up?

13:47.609 --> 13:48.871
- We're following a lead.

13:48.915 --> 13:51.352
We got video
of Regina's boyfriend

13:51.395 --> 13:52.701
running away
from the crime scene.

13:52.744 --> 13:55.835
Not sure if or how
he's related to the murder,

13:55.878 --> 13:57.880
but he's the only game in town
and we're chasing it.

13:57.924 --> 14:00.622
- Well, she definitely didn't
say anything to me about him,

14:00.665 --> 14:02.842
but I was planning
on calling her

14:02.885 --> 14:04.539
to check in with her,
see how she's doing.

14:04.582 --> 14:07.411
So I'm happy to do some digging
if that would be helpful.

14:07.455 --> 14:08.804
- Yeah. That would be good.

14:08.848 --> 14:09.892
- In the meantime,
we're gonna pretend

14:09.936 --> 14:11.589
that conversation
already happened.

14:11.633 --> 14:13.461
Might give us an angle
to leverage the boyfriend,

14:13.504 --> 14:14.679
Gleacher, into cooperating.

14:14.723 --> 14:16.029
- Yeah, worth a shot.

14:16.072 --> 14:17.639
Good luck with
the investigation.

14:17.682 --> 14:19.859
I'll be in touch.
- Thanks.

14:19.902 --> 14:23.906
- You know, it's hard enough
being a cop these days.

14:23.950 --> 14:26.735
Last thing we needed
is losing one of our own.

14:31.479 --> 14:33.089
♪

14:33.133 --> 14:34.656
- Like we said the
last time we talked,

14:34.699 --> 14:36.701
we got you on video
running down Broadway.

14:36.745 --> 14:39.922
We also now know that
you're dating a teenage girl

14:39.966 --> 14:41.750
named Regina Daniels.

14:41.793 --> 14:44.318
- Who had a bruise and eight
stitches above her right eye.

14:44.361 --> 14:45.928
- We're not sure how
all of this connected

14:45.972 --> 14:47.582
to Jimmy Doyle's murder,

14:47.625 --> 14:49.062
but for some reason,
I know it is.

14:49.105 --> 14:50.977
Call it my Irish instinct
for tragedy.

14:51.020 --> 14:52.456
- And if you know something,
now is the time

14:52.500 --> 14:53.849
to get out in front of it.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.895
- Well, my client
is happy to cooperate,

14:55.938 --> 14:57.809
but we're going to
need full immunity

14:57.853 --> 15:00.638
for any potential charges
relating to Regina Daniels.

15:00.682 --> 15:02.771
- Well, if he's so innocent,
why is he demanding immunity?

15:02.814 --> 15:04.599
- Because Regina's nuts.

15:04.642 --> 15:06.644
She gets emotional
and irrational.

15:06.688 --> 15:08.342
- Of course she's emotional
and irrational.

15:08.385 --> 15:09.952
She's 19. You don't like it?

15:09.996 --> 15:12.389
Don't date teenagers.
- And don't hit them.

15:12.433 --> 15:13.782
- Look, guys, it's simple.

15:13.825 --> 15:15.479
Either we get immunity
or we don't talk.

15:15.523 --> 15:16.959
- Watch yourself, Carl.

15:17.003 --> 15:18.439
You're playing hardball
with the wrong guy

15:18.482 --> 15:20.006
and the wrong case.

15:20.049 --> 15:22.922
We can arrest his smug little
Wall Street ass right now.

15:22.965 --> 15:24.445
- Hell of a headline.

15:24.488 --> 15:26.534
"Founder of TeamGirl
arrested for beating up

15:26.577 --> 15:28.405
a 19-year-old female employee."

15:28.449 --> 15:29.841
- I never laid a hand on her!

15:29.885 --> 15:31.147
- Were you involved in
his murder, yes or no?

15:31.191 --> 15:33.106
- No! But I know who was.

15:33.149 --> 15:35.369
- Easy. Easy. Easy.
[whispering]

15:35.412 --> 15:37.414
- You know
who shot Jimmy Doyle?

15:39.025 --> 15:40.983
- Yes, but I'm not
saying another word

15:41.027 --> 15:43.029
unless I get immunity.

15:43.072 --> 15:45.509
[tense music]

15:45.553 --> 15:47.729
♪

15:51.385 --> 15:51.559
.

15:51.602 --> 15:53.126
- Gleacher claims he
knows who killed Doyle.

15:53.169 --> 15:55.215
- Right.

15:55.258 --> 15:57.304
And he's not going to give us
a name unless we immunize him?

15:57.347 --> 16:00.089
- Even though he swears
he never touched her.

16:00.133 --> 16:02.178
- I just got off the phone
with Benson

16:02.222 --> 16:05.529
and Regina says she knows
nothing about the shooting.

16:05.573 --> 16:07.053
All right?

16:07.096 --> 16:08.402
Also says she's not
interested in pursuing

16:08.445 --> 16:09.620
a criminal case
against Gleacher.

16:09.664 --> 16:11.492
- Right. She just happened

16:11.535 --> 16:14.060
to fall and hit her head
on a table.

16:14.103 --> 16:18.499
- Look, Sam, no one's trying to
give a free pass to an abuser.

16:18.542 --> 16:21.328
But it sounds like the
odds of this woman, Regina,

16:21.371 --> 16:23.156
coming forward isn't great.

16:23.199 --> 16:24.679
And even
if she did come forward,

16:24.722 --> 16:26.681
the odds of getting
a conviction aren't great.

16:26.724 --> 16:29.292
So, as disgusting as it is,

16:29.336 --> 16:31.164
we need to make a deal
with this guy.

16:31.207 --> 16:32.600
- Like I said, our policy--

16:32.643 --> 16:34.428
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
A cop just got murdered.

16:34.471 --> 16:36.386
I don't really care
about your policy.

16:36.430 --> 16:38.606
We need to make a deal
with this prick now.

16:38.649 --> 16:42.131
So call whoever you got to
call--Price, McCoy, the Pope.

16:42.175 --> 16:43.872
Just do whatever you gotta do

16:43.915 --> 16:46.614
to make sure
that we make this deal.

16:46.657 --> 16:49.573
[tense music]

16:49.617 --> 16:55.144
♪

16:57.755 --> 17:00.410
- You tell us what you know,
what you saw,

17:00.454 --> 17:03.544
and then if we believe you,

17:03.587 --> 17:04.893
we'll agree to immunize you

17:04.936 --> 17:07.243
from any potential
criminal charges

17:07.287 --> 17:10.420
Regina Daniels might file in
connection with the injuries

17:10.464 --> 17:12.379
she sustained on April 18th.

17:12.422 --> 17:15.556
Any other charges or claims
before or after that date

17:15.599 --> 17:17.166
don't apply.

17:17.210 --> 17:18.559
Understand?
- Okay.

17:18.602 --> 17:20.169
That's fair enough.

17:20.213 --> 17:21.475
Just tell them what happened.

17:21.518 --> 17:22.737
No need to hold back.

17:24.565 --> 17:27.133
- After the charity event,
I went to meet up

17:27.176 --> 17:29.483
with Regina at her apartment.

17:29.526 --> 17:30.788
I started walking over there,

17:30.832 --> 17:33.661
but her sister Kendra
confronted me,

17:33.704 --> 17:36.229
told me to stay the hell away
from Regina.

17:36.272 --> 17:38.666
She just got back from Miami,

17:38.709 --> 17:40.407
saw the cut
near her sister's eye,

17:40.450 --> 17:42.104
and went crazy.

17:42.148 --> 17:43.279
She never liked me.

17:43.323 --> 17:45.542
Never approved
of our relationship.

17:45.586 --> 17:47.631
She started calling
me all kinds of names,

17:47.675 --> 17:49.242
making crazy accusations.

17:49.285 --> 17:50.634
I told her she was wrong,

17:50.678 --> 17:52.201
that I'd never lay a hand
on her sister

17:52.245 --> 17:54.464
or anybody else
for that matter.

17:54.508 --> 17:57.380
But...she was going nuts.

17:57.424 --> 17:59.643
I tried to walk away,
but she pulled a gun.

17:59.687 --> 18:01.950
Told me if I ever got
near Regina again,

18:01.993 --> 18:04.257
she'd "put my white ass
in the ground."

18:04.300 --> 18:06.128
She meant it too.

18:06.172 --> 18:09.436
Then, out of nowhere,
I hear someone yell "NYPD."

18:09.479 --> 18:11.612
I look to my left
and see some guy

18:11.655 --> 18:13.614
hurrying toward us.

18:13.657 --> 18:17.618
Kendra takes off running,
so I take off too.

18:17.661 --> 18:20.708
About 15 seconds later,
I heard two gunshots.

18:22.797 --> 18:24.799
- Yeah, I saw Gleacher
that night.

18:24.842 --> 18:26.801
I told him he was too old
to be dating my sister.

18:26.844 --> 18:29.673
- Okay, why not just say that
the other day?

18:29.717 --> 18:32.285
- I didn't want Regina to know
that I confronted him.

18:32.328 --> 18:33.634
- Hmm.

18:33.677 --> 18:35.418
Did you and Gleacher
get into an argument?

18:35.462 --> 18:37.551
- No. Not really.

18:37.594 --> 18:38.943
We just talked.

18:38.987 --> 18:40.641
- Hmm.

18:40.684 --> 18:42.817
- Regina's only 19 years old,

18:42.860 --> 18:45.646
and he was playing her
like some kind of toy.

18:45.689 --> 18:47.517
But she was falling in love.

18:47.561 --> 18:48.953
- During the course
of your conversation,

18:48.997 --> 18:50.825
did you encounter
an off-duty police officer?

18:50.868 --> 18:52.348
- No.

18:52.392 --> 18:55.351
- Did you hear any gunshots?
- No.

18:55.395 --> 18:57.266
- We know you're lying, Kendra.

18:57.310 --> 18:59.573
We searched your place
while you were at work

18:59.616 --> 19:02.358
and found blood on your jacket
and your shoes.

19:04.012 --> 19:05.840
- Kendra Daniels,
you're under arrest

19:05.883 --> 19:08.538
for the murder
of Detective Jimmy Doyle.

19:10.540 --> 19:12.673
- I'm just glad we were able
to get an arrest

19:12.716 --> 19:14.588
in such a short period of time.

19:14.631 --> 19:17.373
I know that Jimmy's family
is grieving,

19:17.417 --> 19:20.811
but hopefully this can
help their grieving process

19:20.855 --> 19:22.944
in some small way.

19:22.987 --> 19:26.426
And on a personal note,
I just want to say that...

19:28.079 --> 19:29.429
This one really hurts.

19:30.821 --> 19:32.562
But, Jack,

19:32.606 --> 19:34.608
we're here to support you
and your team

19:34.651 --> 19:36.479
moving forward,
so anything you need,

19:36.523 --> 19:37.741
just let us know.

19:37.785 --> 19:40.353
- Thank you.

19:40.396 --> 19:43.225
- Jack, where are we
from a legal standpoint?

19:43.269 --> 19:44.835
- We're still
collecting evidence,

19:44.879 --> 19:46.359
but right now the biggest issue

19:46.402 --> 19:48.361
is we don't know
why the defendant

19:48.404 --> 19:50.319
actually shot
Detective Doyle.

19:50.363 --> 19:51.538
- I understand,
but let me be clear.

19:51.581 --> 19:53.453
This case is extremely
important to us.

19:53.496 --> 19:55.890
This city is under siege.

19:55.933 --> 19:58.545
Criminals are getting
more brazen by the minute.

19:58.588 --> 20:00.851
Anti-police sentiment
is at an all-time high.

20:00.895 --> 20:05.639
There's a march every other
week demanding to defund us,

20:05.682 --> 20:07.902
for God's sake.

20:07.945 --> 20:11.906
So we have to do everything
that we can to heal this city,

20:11.949 --> 20:14.387
to get justice
for a decorated police officer,

20:14.430 --> 20:16.606
and to protect the men
and women wearing blue.

20:19.914 --> 20:22.438
So you need to send a message.

20:23.613 --> 20:25.746
You shoot a cop,

20:25.789 --> 20:28.314
you will spend the rest
of your damn life in prison.

20:28.357 --> 20:30.794
[tense music]

20:30.838 --> 20:37.627
♪

20:40.413 --> 20:40.587
.

20:40.630 --> 20:42.676
- The DNA on the
shoes and jacket

20:42.719 --> 20:44.808
are a match to Detective Doyle.

20:44.852 --> 20:47.376
- Okay. So she's our shooter.

20:47.420 --> 20:49.291
- Yes, that seems pretty clear.

20:49.335 --> 20:51.685
- What's not so clear
is what caused Kendra Daniels

20:51.728 --> 20:53.164
to pull the trigger.

20:53.208 --> 20:54.688
We still don't have
any eyewitnesses

20:54.731 --> 20:56.211
or surveillance video.

20:56.255 --> 20:58.126
- So it's her word
against Doyle's.

20:58.169 --> 21:00.215
The problem is, he's dead.

21:00.259 --> 21:02.348
- So we work with
the evidence we have,

21:02.391 --> 21:05.307
use that to paint the portrait
of what actually happened.

21:05.351 --> 21:08.092
- Let's start with the
defendant, Kendra Daniels.

21:08.136 --> 21:10.704
She's got a good job,
good reputation, no priors.

21:10.747 --> 21:13.576
- Not the first Girl Scout
to shoot and kill someone.

21:13.620 --> 21:15.665
If she wanted
to protect her sister,

21:15.709 --> 21:17.537
she should've
called the police.

21:17.580 --> 21:20.148
- I get it, but some people
in some communities

21:20.191 --> 21:23.107
don't really trust the police.

21:23.151 --> 21:25.501
- The bottom line is...

21:25.545 --> 21:28.852
she threatened Gleacher
with a handgun,

21:28.896 --> 21:31.246
a police officer saw
what was happening,

21:31.290 --> 21:32.900
intervened, and now he's dead.

21:32.943 --> 21:36.164
She has to pay
the consequences.

21:36.207 --> 21:38.384
- I agree, but like I said,

21:38.427 --> 21:40.342
it's more complicated
than that.

21:40.386 --> 21:43.127
According to the defendant,
Detective Doyle

21:43.171 --> 21:46.392
used a racial invective
while apprehending her,

21:46.435 --> 21:49.743
further escalating her already
heightened emotional state.

21:49.786 --> 21:52.615
There is no doubt she has
to pay the consequences.

21:52.659 --> 21:56.358
My question is
what's the appropriate charge?

21:56.402 --> 21:58.404
- Excuse me?

21:58.447 --> 22:01.450
- All we know is a woman
in a heightened emotional state

22:01.494 --> 22:03.452
shot a cop
who tried to apprehend her.

22:03.496 --> 22:04.671
It's like a Rorschach test.

22:04.714 --> 22:07.543
You can see
what you want to see.

22:07.587 --> 22:12.592
- I don't care what anyone
wants to see, Nolan.

22:12.635 --> 22:14.681
I care about the evidence.

22:14.724 --> 22:18.293
Base your decision
on the facts and the law.

22:18.337 --> 22:19.729
Nothing else.

22:19.773 --> 22:22.689
[soft dramatic music]

22:22.732 --> 22:26.910
♪

22:26.954 --> 22:30.697
- Docket number CR373997-22,

22:30.740 --> 22:32.742
People v. Kendra Daniels.

22:32.786 --> 22:34.440
Aggravated manslaughter
in the first degree.

22:34.483 --> 22:36.224
- Manslaughter?
Are you kidding me?

22:36.267 --> 22:37.791
[gavel bangs]
- Quiet.

22:37.834 --> 22:39.793
How does the defendant plead?

22:39.836 --> 22:41.621
- Not guilty, Your Honor.

22:41.664 --> 22:43.884
- Mr. Price, bail?
- $3 million.

22:43.927 --> 22:46.626
- Your Honor,
the defendant has no priors,

22:46.669 --> 22:48.454
has long-standing ties
to the community--

22:48.497 --> 22:50.586
- Bail is set at $3 million.

22:50.630 --> 22:51.805
[gavel bangs]
Next case.

22:51.848 --> 22:53.328
- You're a coward, Price!

22:53.372 --> 22:54.503
- Might as well give
her a free pass!

22:54.547 --> 22:55.809
- That's enough!
[gavel bangs]

22:55.852 --> 22:58.725
[indistinct chatter]

23:00.466 --> 23:01.902
- [sighs]

23:03.686 --> 23:05.862
- Price.
What the hell was that?

23:05.906 --> 23:07.864
Aggravated manslaughter?

23:07.908 --> 23:10.214
- The best I could do based
on the facts, all right?

23:10.258 --> 23:12.565
Good news is it's winnable,
it's still 20 years in prison.

23:12.608 --> 23:13.827
- She shot a cop.

23:13.870 --> 23:15.568
- I know you're upset,
but this case

23:15.611 --> 23:17.221
isn't as straightforward
as you think.

23:17.265 --> 23:18.919
There's no witnesses, no video.

23:18.962 --> 23:20.964
The only two people
who know what really happened

23:21.008 --> 23:22.444
are Doyle and the defendant.

23:22.488 --> 23:23.880
- Don't give me that crap.

23:23.924 --> 23:27.449
Kendra Daniels pumped two
shiny ones into his chest,

23:27.493 --> 23:29.364
and that's murder one
all day long.

23:29.408 --> 23:30.974
- With all due respect--
- Don't "all due respect" me.

23:31.018 --> 23:34.369
- Fine.
You can preach all day long,

23:34.413 --> 23:36.893
but it doesn't actually
mean anything.

23:36.937 --> 23:39.374
You can't prove
what actually happened.

23:39.418 --> 23:40.984
You can only guess.
That's the issue.

23:41.028 --> 23:42.856
We don't know what happened.

23:42.899 --> 23:44.640
And in this political climate,

23:44.684 --> 23:46.686
there's no way a jury
is going to convict a woman

23:46.729 --> 23:49.036
for murder one
based on these facts.

23:49.079 --> 23:50.864
- You mean there's no way
they're ever going to convict

23:50.907 --> 23:53.997
a Black woman
for shooting a white cop.

23:54.041 --> 23:55.564
That's what you're
really saying, isn't it?

23:55.608 --> 23:57.000
Because if Kendra Daniels
was white--

23:57.044 --> 23:59.568
- But she's not. She's Black.

23:59.612 --> 24:01.875
There's a certain reality
to that fact

24:01.918 --> 24:04.878
that if you don't
understand that,

24:04.921 --> 24:07.924
or you can't appreciate that,
that's on you.

24:07.968 --> 24:09.491
I'm doing the best I can

24:09.535 --> 24:11.667
with the facts
and the evidence I have.

24:11.711 --> 24:13.277
I'm sorry you don't approve,

24:13.321 --> 24:15.976
but don't you dare question
my integrity.

24:16.019 --> 24:17.891
- Or what?
- Hey!

24:17.934 --> 24:19.806
That's enough.

24:19.849 --> 24:21.416
The man's just doing his job.

24:21.460 --> 24:23.636
- His job is to prosecute
Kendra Daniels

24:23.679 --> 24:25.420
to the fullest extent
of the law,

24:25.464 --> 24:27.901
not make excuses for her
just because she's Black.

24:27.944 --> 24:30.730
- Hey, give me a second, Price?

24:30.773 --> 24:33.689
[tense music]

24:33.733 --> 24:35.038
♪

24:35.082 --> 24:36.823
Hey, man.

24:36.866 --> 24:38.433
You gotta back down.

24:38.477 --> 24:40.914
- That woman shot and killed
Jimmy Doyle, Kev.

24:40.957 --> 24:42.611
And she knew
he was a police officer.

24:42.655 --> 24:44.047
That's it.
That's all that matters.

24:44.091 --> 24:45.832
- That's what you believe,
Frank?

24:45.875 --> 24:47.486
Hmm?

24:47.529 --> 24:49.488
You believe it's that simple?

24:49.531 --> 24:51.533
A Black woman and a white cop?

24:51.577 --> 24:52.752
Hmm?

24:52.795 --> 24:57.974
♪

24:59.889 --> 25:01.543
- Hey, Price.
- Yeah.

25:01.587 --> 25:04.067
- Frank is a good man.

25:04.111 --> 25:07.331
Says what he feels, and right
now he's feeling a lot of pain.

25:09.551 --> 25:11.727
And for the record...

25:11.771 --> 25:13.990
I respect what you're doing.

25:14.034 --> 25:16.471
Takes a lot of guts
to stare down NYPD

25:16.515 --> 25:17.733
on a case like this.

25:17.777 --> 25:24.697
♪

25:30.572 --> 25:30.964
.

25:31.007 --> 25:33.880
- I put my arms up
and begged her not to shoot me

25:33.923 --> 25:37.884
when I heard someone yell
"NYPD, don't move."

25:37.927 --> 25:41.148
So I turned to look
and I saw a man

25:41.191 --> 25:44.368
in regular street clothes
rushing toward us.

25:44.412 --> 25:47.110
- What did the defendant do?
- She started running.

25:47.154 --> 25:48.503
- And what did you do?

25:48.547 --> 25:50.418
- I started running too.

25:50.461 --> 25:53.073
- And you're certain
you heard Detective Doyle

25:53.116 --> 25:56.032
identify himself as NYPD?

25:56.076 --> 25:57.904
- Yes.

25:57.947 --> 25:59.296
- Nothing further.

26:03.562 --> 26:07.304
- You've been immunized
from any criminal charges

26:07.348 --> 26:09.306
relating to your physical abuse

26:09.350 --> 26:11.308
of Kendra's little sister,
Regina, correct?

26:11.352 --> 26:12.788
- Objection.

26:12.832 --> 26:14.877
There's no evidence
that Mr. Gleacher abused

26:14.921 --> 26:16.923
or assaulted Regina Daniels.

26:16.966 --> 26:19.882
- Sustained.
Watch yourself, Mr. Harris.

26:20.927 --> 26:24.104
- When Detective Doyle
approached you and Kendra,

26:24.147 --> 26:26.846
you both ran off
in different directions,

26:26.889 --> 26:28.456
correct?
- Yes.

26:28.499 --> 26:33.156
- But Detective Doyle
pursued Kendra, not you.

26:33.200 --> 26:34.593
- Correct.

26:34.636 --> 26:37.900
- In your opinion,
was Detective Doyle

26:37.944 --> 26:42.949
close enough to you and Kendra
to determine your skin color?

26:42.992 --> 26:45.125
- Objection.
Calls for speculation.

26:45.168 --> 26:48.215
- Overruled.
Answer the question.

26:48.258 --> 26:51.174
- Yes, it's possible
he was close enough

26:51.218 --> 26:53.655
to see the color of our skin.

26:53.699 --> 26:56.527
- Nothing further.

26:56.571 --> 26:58.312
- Mr. Gleacher,
were you brandishing

26:58.355 --> 27:00.488
a firearm that night?
- No.

27:00.531 --> 27:04.274
- Was the defendant brandishing
a firearm that night?

27:04.318 --> 27:06.929
- Yes.
- Nothing further.

27:06.973 --> 27:09.018
- You may step down,
Mr. Gleacher.

27:10.629 --> 27:13.544
Okay, next witness.

27:13.588 --> 27:16.286
- Prosecution rests.
- Mr. Harris?

27:16.330 --> 27:20.421
- Defense calls
Detective Michelle Pierce.

27:24.120 --> 27:27.384
[soft dramatic music]

27:27.428 --> 27:31.084
- Internal Affairs.

27:31.127 --> 27:34.130
- Oh. Okay.

27:34.174 --> 27:36.437
Pull up any complaints
involving Doyle right away.

27:36.480 --> 27:39.222
Your Honor, may we speak
in chambers please?

27:40.746 --> 27:42.443
- Your Honor,
we intend to prove

27:42.486 --> 27:44.532
Detective Doyle was racist,

27:44.575 --> 27:47.578
that he confronted
Kendra Daniels

27:47.622 --> 27:49.319
because of his racism,

27:49.363 --> 27:52.192
and that he, in effect,
provoked his own death.

27:52.235 --> 27:54.237
- Whether or not
Doyle was racist

27:54.281 --> 27:56.022
is irrelevant to this case.

27:56.065 --> 27:58.024
It has nothing to do
with the actual shooting.

27:58.067 --> 28:00.679
Kendra Daniels was
threatening Scott Gleacher

28:00.722 --> 28:03.029
with a 9-milimeter Glock.

28:03.072 --> 28:05.596
Doyle saw the gun,
the argument,

28:05.640 --> 28:08.382
and intervened in what he
assumed was an armed robbery.

28:08.425 --> 28:10.427
He didn't choose
to get involved

28:10.471 --> 28:12.560
because Kendra was Black.

28:12.603 --> 28:16.346
And moreover, to introduce this
type of inflammatory evidence

28:16.390 --> 28:19.480
is clearly more prejudicial
than probative.

28:19.523 --> 28:22.135
- Detective Doyle's
relationship to race

28:22.178 --> 28:24.050
is the foundation
of our defense

28:24.093 --> 28:27.923
and nothing can be
more relevant or probative.

28:27.967 --> 28:31.318
Race was the reason
Doyle pursued Kendra

28:31.361 --> 28:33.059
instead of Gleacher.

28:33.102 --> 28:36.323
The reason he didn't
listen to or trust

28:36.366 --> 28:37.628
what Kendra was saying

28:37.672 --> 28:39.587
and ultimately the reason

28:39.630 --> 28:42.242
she was forced to shoot
and kill him.

28:42.285 --> 28:45.071
- Your Honor, it is clear that
Mr. Harris is trying to divert

28:45.114 --> 28:47.551
the jury's attention
from the actual facts

28:47.595 --> 28:51.164
by putting Detective Doyle
on trial for two prior,

28:51.207 --> 28:54.297
unsubstantiated
Internal Affairs complaints.

28:54.341 --> 28:57.039
And for God's sake,
haven't we all learned a lesson

28:57.083 --> 28:58.954
from the OJ Simpson debacle?

28:58.998 --> 29:00.782
Do we really want
to go down that path again?

29:00.826 --> 29:03.480
- I do not need a lecture,
Mr. Price.

29:03.524 --> 29:05.308
I agree with the defense.

29:05.352 --> 29:07.180
The victim's
relationship with race

29:07.223 --> 29:09.095
is integral to their case,

29:09.138 --> 29:13.012
which means the two prior
Internal Affairs investigations

29:13.055 --> 29:17.146
are relevant and will provide
context for the confrontation

29:17.190 --> 29:20.106
between Detective Doyle
and the defendant.

29:20.149 --> 29:23.109
- How can two Internal Affairs
investigations

29:23.152 --> 29:28.505
from over 10 years ago possibly
provide context to this murder?

29:28.549 --> 29:30.464
- I'm allowing it.

29:30.507 --> 29:31.987
- Must be an election year.

29:32.031 --> 29:33.510
- Watch it, Price.

29:33.554 --> 29:37.166
One more word, and I will
hold you in contempt.

29:39.342 --> 29:41.518
- Please state your name
and job title.

29:41.562 --> 29:43.129
- Michelle Pierce.

29:43.172 --> 29:44.652
I'm a detective in
the New York Police Department,

29:44.695 --> 29:46.480
Internal Affairs Division.

29:46.523 --> 29:49.222
- Has your department
ever investigated

29:49.265 --> 29:51.093
Detective James Doyle?

29:51.137 --> 29:52.660
- Yes.
- How many times?

29:52.703 --> 29:54.401
- Twice.

29:54.444 --> 29:58.405
- And what were the nature
of these investigations?

29:58.448 --> 30:02.148
- Both investigations involved
assault and battery complaints.

30:02.191 --> 30:04.280
- Could you tell us
who the complainants were?

30:06.587 --> 30:11.679
These are copies
of the actual legal complaints.

30:11.722 --> 30:14.682
Feel free to refer to them
to refresh your memory.

30:17.380 --> 30:21.167
- The first complainant
was named Philip Jackson.

30:21.210 --> 30:23.647
The second complainant
was named Travis Fairmont.

30:23.691 --> 30:26.302
- What were
the specific allegations?

30:27.564 --> 30:31.090
- For Philip Jackson,
"The police officer grabbed me

30:31.133 --> 30:35.529
"called me a punk-ass N-word,
threw me into a wall,

30:35.572 --> 30:39.533
then punched me in the face
three times."

30:39.576 --> 30:42.710
- Now Travis Fairmont.

30:42.753 --> 30:45.408
- "The police officer
repeatedly hit me in the back

30:45.452 --> 30:48.411
"with his nightstick,
kicked me in the stomach,

30:48.455 --> 30:51.066
"then called me various
racial slurs,

30:51.110 --> 30:55.201
including the N-word."

30:55.244 --> 30:57.725
- In both instances,
the complainants

30:57.768 --> 31:02.295
referred to a police officer.

31:02.338 --> 31:04.166
Could you please clarify

31:04.210 --> 31:06.603
the name
of that police officer?

31:06.647 --> 31:08.605
- Detective James Doyle.

31:11.260 --> 31:12.566
- Nothing further.

31:12.609 --> 31:15.525
[tense music]

31:15.569 --> 31:21.575
♪

31:22.924 --> 31:24.926
- There were two
investigations, correct?

31:24.970 --> 31:26.101
- Yes.

31:28.364 --> 31:32.586
- Both of the investigations
took place over 10 years ago

31:32.629 --> 31:34.327
and neither one of them

31:34.370 --> 31:36.546
resulted in any
disciplinary action

31:36.590 --> 31:39.114
being taken against
Detective Doyle, correct?

31:39.158 --> 31:40.768
- Yes, that's correct.

31:40.811 --> 31:43.336
- So he was essentially
found innocent of the charges?

31:43.379 --> 31:44.641
- Yes.

31:46.643 --> 31:49.429
- As for the two men
who filed the complaints,

31:49.472 --> 31:53.215
one of them was charged
with aggravated rape,

31:53.259 --> 31:55.174
the other was charged
with the murder

31:55.217 --> 31:58.177
of a seven-year-old girl.

31:58.220 --> 31:59.613
- That's correct.

32:01.310 --> 32:05.924
- So the two men who accused
Detective Doyle of racism

32:05.967 --> 32:08.361
were both degenerate criminals.

32:08.404 --> 32:11.277
- Objection.
- Sustained.

32:11.320 --> 32:12.669
- Nothing further.

32:12.713 --> 32:19.241
♪

32:22.766 --> 32:22.941
.

32:22.984 --> 32:25.421
- The judge is giving the
defense whatever it wants.

32:25.465 --> 32:27.162
She's losing sight
of the facts, the law.

32:27.206 --> 32:28.990
- I know.

32:29.034 --> 32:31.384
Good news is you bought back
most of the damage on cross

32:31.427 --> 32:33.125
and the jury's not stupid.

32:33.168 --> 32:34.822
They'll understand
that those complaints

32:34.865 --> 32:37.303
were really just pathetic
attempts to discredit Doyle.

32:37.346 --> 32:39.000
- How can you let them
do that to Jimmy?

32:39.044 --> 32:40.480
- Ma'am--

32:40.523 --> 32:42.482
- You just sat there
and watched while that lawyer

32:42.525 --> 32:44.832
tore apart his reputation,
his legacy!

32:44.875 --> 32:46.355
- I'm sorry, I know that
must've been unpleasant.

32:46.399 --> 32:47.835
- Jimmy was a good man

32:47.878 --> 32:50.011
and he died
trying to do a good thing.

32:50.055 --> 32:51.752
He is a hero, for God's sakes.

32:51.795 --> 32:53.232
And what they are doing
to him--

32:53.275 --> 32:55.799
I have three kids.

32:56.931 --> 32:58.498
That crap is gonna follow them
until the day they die.

32:58.541 --> 33:00.195
When they google
their father's name,

33:00.239 --> 33:03.720
it'll say "racist cop,"
and that is not okay!

33:08.421 --> 33:11.032
- She's right, it's not fair.

33:11.076 --> 33:13.382
The problem is there is nothing
we can do about it.

33:13.426 --> 33:16.124
- Well, sure, there is.
We can prove them wrong

33:16.168 --> 33:19.345
and rebut this idea
that Doyle was a racist.

33:21.912 --> 33:24.350
- Maybe we should call
Doyle's girlfriend.

33:24.393 --> 33:26.395
If nothing else,
it proves there's at least

33:26.439 --> 33:30.443
one Black woman out there
he loved and admired.

33:32.314 --> 33:35.796
- Yeah, it might not be enough,
but it's something.

33:36.927 --> 33:39.104
♪

33:39.147 --> 33:42.933
- Ms. Gates, how long did
you and Detective Doyle date?

33:44.109 --> 33:46.067
- Almost three years.

33:46.111 --> 33:48.069
- How would you characterize
your relationship?

33:48.113 --> 33:49.331
- It was amazing.

33:49.375 --> 33:52.378
We loved each other very much.

33:52.421 --> 33:54.336
- Did you think Detective Doyle
was racist?

33:54.380 --> 33:56.382
- No, of course not.

33:58.079 --> 33:59.907
I mean, look at me
for God's sake.

34:01.822 --> 34:03.041
- Thank you.

34:08.133 --> 34:13.051
- Ms. Gates, please direct
your attention to the monitor.

34:13.094 --> 34:16.097
Detective Doyle sent you this
two years ago, correct?

34:16.141 --> 34:17.794
- Yes.

34:17.838 --> 34:20.797
- Your Honor, I'd like
to show the jury this video

34:20.841 --> 34:24.105
in its entirety as it pertains
to whether or not

34:24.149 --> 34:26.107
Detective Doyle was racist.

34:26.151 --> 34:28.196
- Yes, you may show it.

34:28.240 --> 34:30.503
- To my beautiful,
amazing girlfriend

34:30.546 --> 34:33.245
on her 34th birthday.

34:33.288 --> 34:35.508
I don't know what I'd do
without you.

34:35.551 --> 34:37.510
I really don't.

34:37.553 --> 34:40.904
You're one of the best things
that's ever happened to me.

34:40.948 --> 34:43.081
I can't get enough of you,
baby.

34:43.124 --> 34:45.083
I really can't.

34:45.126 --> 34:47.128
Guess Mick Jagger was right.

34:47.172 --> 34:50.175
"Brown sugar is the best kind
of sugar there is."

34:50.218 --> 34:53.178
[tense music]

34:53.221 --> 34:58.574
♪

34:58.618 --> 35:01.142
- I've seen lots of white cops

35:01.186 --> 35:03.492
do horrible things
to Black men and women.

35:05.320 --> 35:07.975
I saw two of them
beat my cousin Ray to a pulp

35:08.018 --> 35:10.282
for having a beer
on the street corner.

35:11.631 --> 35:15.243
So yeah,
I don't trust the police,

35:15.287 --> 35:17.115
white or Black.

35:19.029 --> 35:23.251
- So when Detective Doyle

35:23.295 --> 35:25.166
is charging towards you

35:25.210 --> 35:29.475
with his gun pointed at you,

35:29.518 --> 35:31.041
what did you do?

35:32.478 --> 35:35.176
- I panicked.

35:35.220 --> 35:38.658
I tried to tell him that no
crimes were being committed,

35:38.701 --> 35:40.442
that I wasn't trying
to rob anyone,

35:40.486 --> 35:42.488
but he just kept screaming
at me

35:42.531 --> 35:45.099
to get my black ass
on the ground,

35:45.143 --> 35:47.275
yelling for me
to get on my knees.

35:47.319 --> 35:49.016
- Did that upset him?

35:49.059 --> 35:50.365
- It made him crazy.

35:52.237 --> 35:53.977
He started yelling even louder,

35:54.021 --> 35:56.066
using all kinds
of racial slurs,

35:56.110 --> 36:01.333
demanding me to comply
with his orders.

36:01.376 --> 36:05.337
- Kendra,
why didn't you just do

36:05.380 --> 36:08.601
what Detective Doyle said--
comply?

36:11.212 --> 36:15.216
- I've seen what happens
even when Black people comply,

36:15.260 --> 36:17.262
when they do
what the police tell them.

36:18.480 --> 36:21.222
My cousin Ray complied.

36:21.266 --> 36:23.616
Did what they asked.

36:23.659 --> 36:26.227
They beat him senseless anyway.

36:26.271 --> 36:31.058
- So with Detective Doyle
yelling at you

36:31.101 --> 36:36.194
to get on your knees
with his gun pointed at you...

36:37.978 --> 36:39.240
What did you do?

36:42.069 --> 36:44.550
- I tried to calm him down.

36:44.593 --> 36:48.118
Told him I was just trying
to protect my little sister.

36:48.162 --> 36:51.034
[soft dramatic music]

36:51.078 --> 36:55.300
And then I remembered
that I had a gun in my jacket.

36:55.343 --> 36:56.997
I wanted to make sure
that he knew,

36:57.040 --> 36:59.217
I didn't want him
to be surprised,

36:59.260 --> 37:01.088
so I told him.

37:01.131 --> 37:04.396
♪

37:04.439 --> 37:06.311
But when I--

37:06.354 --> 37:09.096
When I told him,
he just started coming at me

37:09.139 --> 37:11.751
and he had this look
in his eyes.

37:11.794 --> 37:17.583
♪

37:17.626 --> 37:20.150
I thought he was gonna
shoot me.

37:22.544 --> 37:23.763
I really did.

37:26.592 --> 37:31.249
I didn't want to end up like
George Floyd or all the others.

37:32.511 --> 37:37.167
So I did what I did
because I didn't want to die.

37:37.211 --> 37:43.435
♪

37:57.797 --> 38:01.583
- The gun was in your hand,

38:01.627 --> 38:04.673
not your jacket, correct?

38:04.717 --> 38:07.415
- No. It was my in my jacket.

38:09.199 --> 38:14.509
- So with Detective Doyle's
gun trained on you,

38:14.553 --> 38:17.251
you were still somehow
able to retrieve the gun

38:17.295 --> 38:21.560
from your jacket
and shoot him twice?

38:21.603 --> 38:23.518
- That's what happened.

38:23.562 --> 38:27.696
♪

38:27.740 --> 38:30.656
- After you shot
Detective Doyle,

38:30.699 --> 38:32.788
you didn't call 911, correct?

38:35.182 --> 38:36.705
- Correct.

38:36.749 --> 38:40.100
- And you didn't attempt to
render aid either, did you?

38:41.841 --> 38:44.626
- No, I was scared.

38:44.670 --> 38:47.063
I just started running.

38:47.107 --> 38:50.284
- So...

38:50.328 --> 38:54.854
you just left Detective Doyle

38:54.897 --> 38:57.857
on the pavement...

38:57.900 --> 39:00.686
bleeding.

39:00.729 --> 39:02.383
Dying.

39:02.427 --> 39:07.736
♪

39:07.780 --> 39:09.564
- Yes.

39:14.613 --> 39:16.223
- Nothing further.

39:16.266 --> 39:23.230
♪

39:28.496 --> 39:30.368
- Accused and counsel,
please rise.

39:35.198 --> 39:37.418
Madam Foreperson,
how do you find

39:37.462 --> 39:39.246
on the charge
of aggravated manslaughter

39:39.289 --> 39:40.421
in the first degree?

39:40.465 --> 39:43.119
- We find the defendant
not guilty.

39:43.163 --> 39:44.556
[people shouting]
- What?!

39:44.599 --> 39:45.905
[gavel bangs]
- Order!

39:45.948 --> 39:47.472
- You call this justice?

39:47.515 --> 39:49.474
- She killed one of ours!
- Order! Order!

39:49.517 --> 39:51.345
I won't say it again.

39:51.389 --> 39:54.304
[tense dramatic music]

39:54.348 --> 39:56.568
♪

39:56.611 --> 39:58.439
Madam foreperson,
how do you find

39:58.483 --> 40:00.267
on the charge
of aggravated manslaughter

40:00.310 --> 40:01.573
in the second degree?

40:01.616 --> 40:04.489
- We find the defendant guilty.

40:04.532 --> 40:06.360
- Yes!
- She didn't do anything wrong!

40:06.404 --> 40:08.623
- Order!
- She deserves more!

40:08.667 --> 40:10.843
[people shouting]

40:10.886 --> 40:12.584
- Order!
[gavel bangs]

40:12.627 --> 40:14.412
- I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

40:14.455 --> 40:16.718
[people shouting]

40:18.503 --> 40:19.808
- Cop killer!

40:23.333 --> 40:25.466
- You tried a hell of a case,
Nolan.

40:25.510 --> 40:26.772
- Yeah, everyone seemed

40:26.815 --> 40:28.643
to be so happy
with the outcome.

40:30.689 --> 40:32.560
- Sort of the point, isn't it?

40:32.604 --> 40:35.171
When both sides are outraged,

40:35.215 --> 40:37.870
it probably means
it was a good result.

40:37.913 --> 40:39.524
- It doesn't feel so good.

40:41.308 --> 40:44.833
- A really smart prosecutor
once told me...

40:44.877 --> 40:46.618
if you try a good case,

40:46.661 --> 40:48.620
if you do it the right way,

40:48.663 --> 40:51.797
whatever the jury decides
is right,

40:51.840 --> 40:54.495
whether or not it feels good.

40:54.539 --> 40:57.498
[soft dramatic music]

40:57.542 --> 41:04.462
♪

41:22.784 --> 41:25.700
[dramatic music]

41:25.744 --> 41:32.707
♪

41:52.771 --> 41:55.730
[wolf howls]
